/jpeg',0),(88,1,'2015-12-30 22:32:17','2015-12-30 22:32:17','abc \n\n\n\nAfter watching Terry Godwin execute a trick play in practice, Georgia’s interim coach, Bryan McClendon, was having second thoughts about calling it during the second quarter of a bowl game.\n\nHis players and coaches persuaded him otherwise, and it might have been the best decision of McClendon’s short-lived coaching career.\n\nGodwin, a receiver, lined up in the Wildcat, took the snap and threw a 44-yard touchdown pass that got the Bulldogs going and later caught a 17-yard scoring pass in Georgia’s 24-17 win over Penn State in the TaxSlayer Bowl on Saturday in Jacksonville, Fla.\n\n“I think the coaches believe in me enough to put the ball in my hands to make a play,” Godwin said.\n\nThe play helped the Bulldogs (10-3) end the season with their fifth consecutive victory, send McClendon out a winner in his head-coaching debut and give the senior class its 40th career victory.\n\n“It’s why you have to trust the people that are around you,” said McClendon, who was called on to fill in after Coach Mark Richt was fired and opted not to stick around for the bowl game. “They said it was there.”\n\n\n<a href=\"http://52.70.236.130/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/450BF5F2796F4D2EBCF7BDADC7A582CB.ashx_.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-87\"><img src=\"http://52.70.236.130/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/450BF5F2796F4D2EBCF7BDADC7A582CB.ashx_.jpg\" alt=\"&quot;The team&quot;\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1600\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-87\" /></a>','abc abc','','publish','open','closed','','abc-abc','','','2016-01-03 04:14:15','2016-01-03 04:14:15','',0,'http://52.70.236.130/events/2015/12/abc-abc/',0,'incsub_event','',3),(92,3,'2015-12-31 15:17:58','2015-12-31 15:17:58','They cheat','TSF','','publish','closed','closed','','tsf','','','2015-12-31 15:17:58','2015-12-31 15:17:58','',69,'http://52.70.236.130/forums/topic/tsf/',0,'topic','',0),(93,3,'2015-12-31 15:19:59','2015-12-31 15:19:59','u13b TSF','TSF u13b